This paper is about generating and defending against adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on developing solutions for generating and defending against adversarial attacks using deep neural networks. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as adversarial examples are often studied in the context of image classification tasks. The third most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks and defenses. The fourth most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as adversarial examples are a well-known challenge in the field of AI. The fifth most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper specifically focuses on deep neural networks and their vulnerability to adversarial attacks.
